What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

class Counter {
public:
    int value;
    void increment() { value += 1; }
    void add(int n)   { value += n; }
};

int main() {
    Counter a;
    a.value = 0;
    Counter b;
    b.value = 10;
    a.increment();
    b.add(5);
    a.add(b.value);
    std::cout << a.value << "\n";
    std::cout << b.value << "\n";
}
```

This `setWidth` function is supposed to update the member `width`, but it doesn't. What is the bug?

```cpp
